    "This approach has been extensively utilized in meta-learning and continual learning frameworks, as shown by several studies [44] [45] [46] [47] [48] [49].",
    "Latest improvements in adaptive subspace learning methods have demonstrated significant improvements in generalization and robustness, especially in challenging environments 50, 51.",
    "Furthermore, incorporation of subspace learning into neural architecture search has proven invaluable in identifying efficient and innovative architectures, optimizing both performance and resource utilization [51] [52] [53].",
